@node Over "Overview"

@{b}Overview
--------@{ub}

These are the Amiga and Windows ports of Koules 1.4, a popular arcade
game for various platforms.

Features include: 1-5 players, sound, triple keyboard and quadruple
joystick/gamepad support, source code.
  The following features of the Linux and/or OS/2 versions are not
implemented in the Amiga and Windows versions:

    * network support
    * user-selectable playfield size
    * 3D intros/outros
    * fullscreen mode
    * analog joystick support (Amiga)

                                 -----
                                /     \\
                               | o | o |
===========================OO==============OO=============================

Koules is a fast action arcade-style game for UNIX, OS/2, AmigaOS 3,
AmigaOS 4, MorphOS, AROS, Windows et al. It has cool graphics,
multi-player mode up to 5 players and sound.
@endnode

@node Requ "System Requirements"

@{b}System Requirements
-------------------@{ub}

This is for the AmigaOS 3.x version of Koules:

@{b}Hardware@{ub}             Required        68020+
                                     about 512K free RAM
                                     640*512 or larger Workbench
                     Recommended     800*600 or larger Workbench
                                     Joystick(s)
                                     CD32 controller(s)
                                     RTG
                                     FPU
                                     OS4/MorphOS
                                     Sound card
                                     Mouse/trackball
@{b}Firmware@{ub}             Required        Kickstart 3.1+
@{b}Software@{ub}             Required        OS3.1+
                     Recommended     OS3.5+
                                     AHI

A very fast Amiga is required to run the game at full speed. This
game runs @{i}much@{ui} faster on an RTG screen than on an AGA screen, as it uses
chunky graphics.
  The AmigaOS 3 version uses Paula via the audio.device. If you remove the
#define USE_PAULA and recompile, you can use AHI sound instead.
  The AmigaOS 4 version uses AHI.
  If you only have a 640*512 Workbench, a borderless window filling the
entire screen will be used.
  If you have OS3.5+, you will be able to iconify/uniconify the window.
@endnode

@node Usag "Usage"

@{b}Usage
-----@{ub}

@{b}CLI Arguments@{ub}

                                   @{b}Koules@{ub}

@{b}Format:    KOULES-FPU@{ub}   [PUBSCREEN <pubscreen>]
        or @{b}KOULES-NOFPU@{ub} [PUBSCREEN <pubscreen>]

@{b}Template:@{ub}  PUBSCREEN/K

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}   To run the Koules game.

@{b}Specification:@{ub}

    pubscreen=<pubscreen>:
           the name of a public screen to open on (otherwise the default
           public screen is used).

@{b}Workbench Tool Types@{ub}

PUBSCREEN=<pubscreen>

These are equivalent to the relevant CLI arguments.

Most game settings are loaded/saved from/to the Koules.config file.
